        <abstract>
            <p>Encloses Fritz Müller’s letter.</p>
            <p>Is exhibiting butterflies in which variations in the female show a finely graded series. Believes dimorphism can be explained by the selection of the extremes of such a series and the consequent extinction of the intermediates.</p>
        </abstract>
